who have a lot of reputational skin in the game,  

784
01:17:30,080 --> 01:17:35,720
who've invested a lot in building up a reputation 
over time are going to be much more cautious about  

785
01:17:35,720 --> 01:17:43,320
disappointing their customers or risking negative 
feedback than someone nobody's ever heard of. 

786
01:17:45,120 --> 01:17:49,240
And let's be honest, I think it's even more 
extreme in the United States than it is in  

787
01:17:49,240 --> 01:17:54,840
the UK. The relationship people have with 
celebrities is kind of pervy and weird.  

788
01:17:56,160 --> 01:18:02,520
They imbue these people with superpowers. They're 
actors. They didn't actually fly through the air,  

789
01:18:02,520 --> 01:18:09,640
but somehow people treat them with this reverence 
because they're just famous. And the point is,  

790
01:18:09,640 --> 01:18:15,760
it's easy mode. If you are actually pretty 
famous, you are playing that game on easy  

791
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:22,240
mode because so many things which require 
massive reassurance, due diligence, checking,  

792
01:18:22,240 --> 01:18:26,200
you take it to the board and three people on the 
board have never heard of the company so they want  

793
01:18:26,200 --> 01:18:32,560
you to go back and check with so-and-so. 
And then you walk in and you're famous,  

794
01:18:32,560 --> 01:18:38,680
the rules are different. When I say there are 
also these inflection points like escape velocity,  

795
01:18:38,680 --> 01:18:44,760
I always say about Coke that Coke has 
reached a magical level of fame where  

796
01:18:44,760 --> 01:18:53,240
it is your expectation that any shop or bar or 
cafe or bistro style restaurant will stock it. 

797
01:18:54,120 --> 01:18:58,600
I can ask for this anywhere, and if 
they haven't got it's their fault,  

798
01:18:58,600 --> 01:19:06,440
not mine. Now that that's really mega fame. But 
equally in B2B, there's an inflection point in  

799
01:19:06,440 --> 01:19:14,560
B2B marketing, which is that if no one ever got 
fired for buying IBM, we know the famous phrase,  

800
01:19:14,560 --> 01:19:21,360
if you appoint Pricewaterhouse or EY or 
whatever to your audit and something goes wrong,  

801
01:19:21,360 --> 01:19:27,120
everybody blames them. If you appoint someone 
