01:19:44,880 --> 01:19:50,840
ring the client and say, "I'm terribly sorry, the 
BA flight's been delayed." They go, "Oh, well,  

806
01:19:50,840 --> 01:19:59,080
never mind you did your best." And if I ring up 
and say, "The Ryanair flight's been delayed," it's  

807
01:19:59,080 --> 01:20:05,440
not quite the same, is it? I haven't necessarily 
tried. I've skipped on that. You see what I mean?

808
01:20:05,440 --> 01:20:05,880
Yeah.

809
01:20:05,880 --> 01:20:14,920
And so various things, it's not just what things 
are, it's what they mean. And we use brands as  

810
01:20:14,920 --> 01:20:21,400
extended phenotypes to express ourselves 
in all kinds of ways. So this is the other  

811
01:20:21,400 --> 01:20:27,840
thing with brands, it's not just a simple 
consumer. It's not just a simple business  

812
01:20:27,840 --> 01:20:31,880
consumer relationship. There are all kinds 
of things as what does the brand I use say  

813
01:20:31,880 --> 01:20:38,600
about me? It's do the people who know me 
know what this brand means? It's no good  

814
01:20:38,600 --> 01:20:45,040
being a luxury car that only rich people have 
heard of. Because in order to convey prestige,  

815
01:20:45,040 --> 01:20:50,280
it's necessary for you to know that other 
people know that BMW is a prestigious car  

816
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:54,240
brand and so on and so forth. So there are 
lots of things here which are second order,  

817
01:20:54,240 --> 01:21:00,200
third order, non-linear compounding factors. 
We just have to acknowledge this is a different  

818
01:21:00,200 --> 01:21:12,200
kind of maths and yet we're being judged on an X 
minus Y equals Z maths. Doesn't make any sense.

819
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:15,160
Maybe as a final question, is there 
anything you want to leave listeners with,  

820
01:21:15,160 --> 01:21:19,360
folks that are building product? Any 
lasting piece of nugget or advice?

821
01:21:19,360 --> 01:21:28,440
Try and do the psychological and the technological 
and the economic for that matter. In other words,  

822
01:21:28,440 --> 01:21:35,480
the sweet spot is it works psychologically. It 
works technologically and it works economically.  

823
01:21:35,480 --> 01:21:41,160
In other words, you can make money out of 
it. People want it and it allows them to  

824
01:21:41,160 --> 01:21:48,080
do something significantly new by using some 
clever application of tech. Try and use those  

825
01:21:48,080 --> 01:21:53,120
three things in parallel because I think what 
most businesses do is they try and do things in  

826
01:21:53,120 --> 01:21:59,520
series and businesses borrow an awful lot from 
the Fordist Taylorist production line mentality  

827
01:21:59,520 --> 01:22:06,840
of the process. And the process, we have to 
pretend that the process is linear, but the  

828
01:22:06,840 --> 01:22:11,840
process of any kind of innovation or development 
is not linear. They're loads of products, which by  

829
01:22:11,840 --> 01:22:16,760
the way have completely failed at first iteration, 
and then someone sold them in a different way and  

830
01:22:16,760 --> 01:22:26,360
they then turn out to be completely successful.
The Pivot is an example of that. Famously Wrigley  

831
01:22:26,360 --> 01:22:32,000
started off selling soap powder in Chicago. Then 
he started giving away baking powder free to  

832
01:22:32,000 --> 01:22:37,120
sell the soap powder, and then realized he'd start 
making baking powder and selling that, and he gave  

833
01:22:37,120 --> 01:22:43,200
away chewing gum that went on the baking powder 
as a gift. And then people liked the chewing gum  

834
01:22:43,200 --> 01:22:47,760
a lot more than they liked the baking powder. So 
as a result, Wrigley became a chewing gum company. 

835
01:22:49,440 --> 01:22:53,880
But we're always trying to make this thing 
linear because when we tell stories backwards,  

836
01:22:53,880 --> 01:22:59,240
we post-rationalize and we reverse engineer and we 
reverse engineer our actions to make it all seem  

837
01:22:59,240 --> 01:23:05,400
perfectly linear and logical as a self-check. The 
real process is never like that. And I think you  

838
01:23:05,400 --> 01:23:13,400
should have marketing. Marketing and innovation 
are two sides of the same coin. As I often say,  

839
01:23:13,400 --> 01:23:16,760
you can either work out what people want 
to find out a clever way to make it,  

840
01:23:16,760 --> 01:23:22,120
or you can work out what you can make and 
find a clever way to make people want it.  

841
01:23:22,120 --> 01:23:29,120
And actually the greatest things manage to do 
both. Simple as that. Don't do it one than the  

842
01:23:29,120 --> 01:23:35,200
other. Don't leave marketing to the last minute, 
but equally work in parallel as far as you can.

